*****************************************************************************
Non-Standard Dependencies****************************************************
openmpi

*****************************************************************************
Compile the Source code******************************************************
The source code has been designed to run on linux systems.
Running

./makefile

from this directory should compile the source code.
If makefile did not stay executable, one can run

source makefile

*****************************************************************************
Running the Code*************************************************************
The input file is the *.inp file in this directory.
From here, the user can change the basic parameters used to setup and
	solve the explosion wave problem which is default.
To run the simulation, use the run script by typing

./run

into a terminal.  If "run" did not stay executable, you can also run the code
using

source run

after the code is compiled.

Simulation information is stored in the log file after
	the simulation has begun.
Output data is written in .vtk format for analysis in Paraview.

*****************************************************************************
About the Author*************************************************************
Micah Esmond is a Ph.D. candidate at Virginia Tech conducting research in the
	computational modeling of Electrothermal (ET) plasmas.
